com.samskivert.depot.annotation

Annotation Type GeneratedValue


  • @Target(value=FIELD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface GeneratedValue
    Provides for the specification of generation strategies for the values of primary keys. The GeneratedValue annotation may be applied to a primary field in conjunction with the Id annotation.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      int allocationSize
      The amount to increment by when allocating id numbers from the generator.
      String generator
      Identifies which generator should be used to generate this value when using a table or sequence generator.
      int initialValue
      The initial value to be used when allocating id numbers from the generator.
      boolean migrateIfExists
      If there are rows in our corresponding table, this boolean determines whether or not to attempt to initialize the generator to the maximum value of our associated field over those rows.
      GenerationType strategy
      Identifies the strategy to be used to generate this value.

    • Element Detail

      • generator

        public abstract String generator
        Identifies which generator should be used to generate this value when using a table or sequence generator.
        Default:
        ""

      • strategy

        public abstract GenerationType strategy
        Identifies the strategy to be used to generate this value.
        Default:
        com.samskivert.depot.annotation.GenerationType.AUTO

      • initialValue

        public abstract int initialValue
        The initial value to be used when allocating id numbers from the generator. The default initial value is 1. Note: this default differs from the value used by the EJB3 persistence framework.
        Default:
        1

      • migrateIfExists

        public abstract boolean migrateIfExists
        If there are rows in our corresponding table, this boolean determines whether or not to attempt to initialize the generator to the maximum value of our associated field over those rows. This attribute does not exist in the EJB3 framework.
        Default:
        true

      • allocationSize

        public abstract int allocationSize
        The amount to increment by when allocating id numbers from the generator. The default allocation size is 1. Note: this default differs from the value used by the EJB3 persistence framework.
        Default:
        1
